Requirement to add forward security logs to a Windows event collector server:

Add network service to the BUILTIN\Event Log Readers group on each source computer. This can be easily achieved via Group policy Reference.

Group policy object to configure "Target subscription Manager" was enabled in "Default Domain Controllers Policy".

Add "Network Service" SID to security log channel Access via command line.

Run command wevtutil get-log security to get current channel access for security log in Domain controlled servers.

Copy channel access value.

Run command wevtutil set-log security /ca: <Paste-Here-Channel-Access>(A;;0x1;;;S-1-5-20) to include Network Service SID to the security log channel access.

Run command wevtutil get-log security to confirm that network service SID was added successfully.

once this has been done, WinRM service must be restarted on both Domain controller & WEC servers.

After restarting the service, Domain controller security logs should start being forwarded to the collector server. This works on both source initiated and collector initiated subscription.


